An avalanche crashed through a small Austrian resort on Tuesday in what officials feared could turn out to be Austria's worst snow disaster in years.
Driving snow and deadly winds prevented emergency helicopters from flying into the ski village of Galtuer, near the Swiss border, local rescue workers spent the night digging through walls of snow and rubble for survivors.
At least 30 people, some of them injured, were dug out by evening.
